commit.message:
settings: use os.fdatasync() and os.fsync() when available

Improve macOS performance by using the `os.fsync()` and `os.fdatasync()`
functions when available.

This completely removes any code path that calls `os.sync()`.

Related-to: #1305
Signed-off-by: David Aguilar <davvid@gmail.com>

settings: use fsync / fdatasync on Linux to sync contents

Avoid an OS-level sync by using fsync and fdatasync when they are available.

Related-to: #1305
Signed-off-by: David Aguilar <davvid@gmail.com>

settings: avoid syncing when cola.sync is configured to false

We can now inhibit the use of `os.sync()` using `git config`:

    git config --global cola.sync false

Resolves: #1305
Reported-by: @installgentoo via github
Signed-off-by: David Aguilar <davvid@gmail.com>

Merge pull request #1385 from davvid/bindir

* davvid/bindir:
  resources: search for commands sibling to the running script
  resources: remove unnecessary os.path.dirname import

Signed-off-by: David Aguilar <davvid@gmail.com>

resources: search for commands sibling to the running script

When Cola is installed directly into C:\Python3.12 on Windows
then the correct path to git-cola-sequence-editor was not being used.

Look in the same director as the current sprint when attempting to
find git-cola-sequence-editor. This makes cola rely less on the
physical structure of the install tree by checking for locations
relative to itself.

Closes: #1385
Reported-by: Stanislaw Halik <sthalik@misaki.pl>
Signed-off-by: David Aguilar <davvid@gmail.com>

resources: remove unnecessary os.path.dirname import

Signed-off-by: David Aguilar <davvid@gmail.com>

push: prefer the local branch when selecting a corresponding remote branch

We were using the current branch instead of the local branch field when
finding a corresponding remote branch to select. Correct the behavior by
using the local branch text instead.

Related-to: #729
Suggested-by: @pkzc on github.com
Signed-off-by: David Aguilar <davvid@gmail.com>

push: set the remote branch field when selecting a local branch

Keep the behavior of the "Push" dialog closer to the original behavior
where selecting the local branch would implicitly push that remote
branch to the same-named remote branch.

We now clear selections from the remote branch list when a local branch
is clicked. But, we also pre-populate the "Remote Branch" field so that
it's clear that the selected branch will be pushed to the remote.

We can still push a disjoint set of branches by explicitly selecting
a remote branch, but that is more of an uncommon operation.

Closes: #729
Suggested-by: @pkzc on github.com
Signed-off-by: David Aguilar <davvid@gmail.com>

Merge pull request #1387 from davvid/remote-dialog

* davvid/remote-dialog:
  fetch: add support for the traditional FETCH_HEAD behavior
  fetch: add ability to fetch into a remote tracking branch
  tests: prune empty lines and add docstrings
  remote: select remote branch by default
  tests: stop disabling the pytest cache provider

Signed-off-by: David Aguilar <davvid@gmail.com>

fetch: add support for the traditional FETCH_HEAD behavior

Special-case FETCH_HEAD for anonymous fetching into an ephemeral ref.
This allows users to get the original behavior before we defaulted to
fetching into remote tracking branches directly.

Related-to: #729
Signed-off-by: David Aguilar <davvid@gmail.com>

fetch: add ability to fetch into a remote tracking branch

Fetch directly into the remote tracking branch when only the
remote branch is selected in the Fetch dialog.

Related-to: #729
Signed-off-by: David Aguilar <davvid@gmail.com>

tests: prune empty lines and add docstrings

Signed-off-by: David Aguilar <davvid@gmail.com>

remote: select remote branch by default

Special-case when the local branch is the same as the remote branch
when pushing so that we use a simple "<branch>" refspec.

Select the remote branch by default when pushing to make the
user interface more intuitive.

Closes: #729
Signed-off-by: David Aguilar <davvid@gmail.com>

tests: stop disabling the pytest cache provider

pytest-ruff >= 0.3.0 assumes that the cache is present.
Remove the no:cacheprovider argument to allow testing
against newer versions of pytest, pytest-ruff and ruff.

Signed-off-by: David Aguilar <davvid@gmail.com>

commit.message:
git: refactor Paths.get() into two functions to reduce complexity

Signed-off-by: David Aguilar <davvid@gmail.com>

remote: remember the selected remotes

Teach the Fetch, Push and Pull dialogs to remember the selected remotes.
This makes it very convenient to push to a set of remotes repeatedly.

Closes: #729
Signed-off-by: David Aguilar <davvid@gmail.com>

remote: display the git commands for Fetch, Push and Pull

Automatically select the remote branch in the Pull dialog. Display the
git command that will be run in the Fetch, Push and Pull dialogs so that
users can be assured that they know what will be run.

Closes: #729
Signed-off-by: David Aguilar <davvid@gmail.com>

log: allow using the log widget without the usage text

Prepare the log widget for reuse in the Fetch, Push and Pull dialogs.

Related-to: #729
Signed-off-by: David Aguilar <davvid@gmail.com>
